excerpt: 'Tracking the teacherâ€™s position in real-time during the class should be able to increase the appropriateness of the advice that an orchestration system gives to teachers and students. However, such tracking needs to be done accurately without impinging on student privacy. This paper describes both our implementation of a teacher-tracking system and an evaluation of its accuracy in a mathematics middle-school classroom. The tracking system interprets data from an indoor positioning system that has the teacher wear a transmitter whose signals are detected by sensors on the walls of the classroom.'
